msgid "Microsoft Windows Installer"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#, no-wrap
msgid "Description"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"The FusionInventory Agent Microsoft Windows Installer is an open source "
"project than has as goal to build the installer program of the "
"FusionInventory Agent and its tasks for Microsoft Windows operative systems. "
"It makes use of some others open source projects, like the [Nullsoft "
"Scriptable Install System](http://nsis.sourceforge.net/Main_Page)  (in "
"forward NSIS), Strawberry Perl, Curl, etcetera, to obtain its objective."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"It is born to cover a basic goal; be able to install new FusionInventory "
"Agent versions based on the previous configuration in the system, whether it "
"exists.  In summary, it is born to be able to update the existing agent, and "
"not only to install a new version from scratch."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "It has more purposes, of course. The following are some of them."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#, no-wrap
msgid "Features"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid "Installs from scratch or from the current configuration."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid "Uninstalls the previous agent, whether it exists."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid "Prevents multiple installations simultaneously."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"Supports visual installation in multiple languages.  (English and Spanish. "
"French in construction.)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"Builds two different installers for x86 and x64 architectures.  (Each "
"platform uses its native distribution of Strawberry Perl)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid "Builds installers for stable or development versions."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"Supports both installation methods; silent or unattended mode and graphical "
"or visual mode."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid "Allows to select the agent tasks to install."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid "New visual appearance based on the NSIS Modern UI 2 plugin."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"Migrates the depreciated options to the new options and removes completely "
"the obsolete ones from the Microsoft Windows registry."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"Now the Microsoft Windows registry used for agent configuration integrates "
"all the options supported by the agent, and not only those that them values "
"are different to the default."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"Allows a complete customization of all the options supported for the agent, "
"either from the the command line, or from the visual installation."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"Each generated installer is identified uniquely by a BuildID.  (Each "
"architecture has its own BuildID sequence)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"Allows to execute the agent as a Windows Service, to plan its execution "
"through a Windows Task or, simply, not to execute the agent."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"Allows to pull a SSL certificate from a URL at installation time. (TODO)"
msgstr ""

