#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "##How to upgrade the agent and its tasks\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "Let's look at an example."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"   Suppose you know there are new stable releases for FusionInventory-Agent\n"
"and FusionInventory-Agent-Task-Deploy. You have the builder ready to build the\n"
"installers with FusionInventory-Agent v2.2.5, FusionInventory-Agent-Task-Deploy\n"
"v2.0.2, FusionInventory-Agent-Task-ESX v2.2.0 and FusionInventory-Agent-Task-\n"
"-Network v1.0.1 so you want to change it to get the installers with the last\n"
"releases.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"   In GitHub you can find all releases of FusionInventory-Agent and its tasks.\n"
"In https://github.com/fusinv are registered most of the projects of\n"
"FusionInventory but here we are only interested in four of them. They are,\n"
"with their URLs, the following\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"      FusionInventory-Agent\n"
"         https://github.com/fusinv/fusioninventory-agent\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"      FusionInventory-Agent-Task-Deploy\n"
"         https://github.com/fusinv/fusioninventory-agent-task-deploy\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"      FusionInventory-Agent-Task-ESX\n"
"         https://github.com/fusinv/fusioninventory-agent-task-esx\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"      and FusionInventory-Agent-Task-Network\n"
"         https://github.com/fusinv/fusioninventory-agent-task-network\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"   You can see the tag (or release) names, the branch names or the commit names\n"
"of these project the same way you see them of this one. For more information,\n"
"see section 'How to generate the installers' above.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"   By taking a look at https://github.com/fusinv/fusioninventory-agent/tags and\n"
"https://github.com/fusinv/fusioninventory-agent-task-deploy/tags you see those\n"
"new releases are v2.2.6 and v2.0.3 respectively (it is true in the time I am\n"
"writing this). These are the changes you should to carry out.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"   Edit the './Perl/Scripts/load-perl-environment' file and change the value of\n"
"variables 'fusinv_agent_commit' and 'fusinv_task_deploy_commit' to '2.2.6' and\n"
"'2.0.3' respectively. The other variables (fusinv_agent_mod_name, fusinv_agent-\n"
"_repository, fusinv_task_deploy_name and fusinv_task_deploy_repository) should\n"
"maintain its values, unless there are changes in GitHub.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"      -declare +r fusinv_agent_commit='2.2.5'\n"
"      +declare +r fusinv_agent_commit='2.2.6'\n"
"         ...\n"
"      -declare +r fusinv_task_deploy_commit='2.0.2'\n"
"      +declare +r fusinv_task_deploy_commit='2.0.3'\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"[[!template  id=info text=\"Note that, in these cases, '2.2.6' and '2.0.3' are 'tags' in Git\n"
"terminology; that is, in our case, stable releases. A tag makes\n"
"reference, in last term, to a commit, therefore the name of the\n"
"variable.\"]]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"   An important thing to take into account is that, probably, these new releases\n"
"require new, or simply different, Perl modules. Whether it is so, you should\n"
"build a new Strawberry Perl Package for FusionInventory-Agent. But before to do\n"
"that, you should carry out two actions; a) to increase the package build identi-\n"
"fier and b) to update the list of required and recommended Perl modules.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"   To do the first one is easy, you only need to edit the '.\\Perl\\Script\\load-\n"
"-perl-environment' and to increment it in a unit.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"      -declare -r strawberry_pepfia_build_id='1'\n"
"      +declare -r strawberry_pepfia_build_id='2'\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"[[!template  id=info text=\"Note that the variable 'strawberry_pepfia_branch' is not necessary\n"
"to change it in this case since the branch 2.2.x match with the\n"
"branch of FusionInventory-Agent release 2.2.6.\"]]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"The second one is, most of the times, more tedious. You should check whether "
"there is new requirements or recommendations comparing the files 'Makefile."
"PL' of each FusionInventory-Agent package you want to update. Then, whether "
"there are changes, you must update the respective variable "
"'fusinv_agent_mod_depen- dences', 'fusinv_task_deploy_mod_dependences', "
"'fusinv_task_esx_mod_dependences' or 'fusinv_task_network_mod_dependences' "
"of './Perl/Scripts/load-perl-environ- ment' file to reflect these changes."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "Let's look at an example for FusionInventory-Agent."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"In https://github.com/fusinv/fusioninventory-agent/tags you can see all "
"stable releases of FusionInventory-Agent. In that, below '2.2.6.zip - 2.2.6 "
"re- lease' appears the sequence '6f67b7d73c'; the short form for its SHA1 "
"commit.  Do click on it, and after, do click on 'Browse code' (up and "
"right). In the list of files that appears, do click on file 'Makefile.Pl' "
"and write down the list of required and recommended Perl modules (those "
"lines started by 'requires ...' and 'recommends ...', but not those lines "
"started by 'text_requires ...')  commons to all operative systems and those "
"specific for Microsoft Windows (those lines under the condition '($OSNAME eq "
"'MSWin32')'). This list of Perl modules should be the new value of the "
"variable 'fusinv_agent_mod_dependences'. Like this list is different of that "
"for 2.2.5 release (repeat the previous process for '2.2.5.zip - 2.2.5 "
"release') you need change the value of the variable "
"'fusinv_agent_mod_dependences'."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"      -declare -r fusion_agent_mod_dependences='Compress::Zlib Digest::MD5\n"
"       File::Which HTTP::Daemon IO::Socket::SSL LWP LWP::Protocol::https\n"
"       Net::IP Text::Template UNIVERSAL::require Win32::Daemon Win32::Job\n"
"       Win32::OLE Win32::TieRegistry XML::TreePP'\n"
"      +declare -r fusinv_agent_mod_dependences='Compress::Zlib File::Which\n"
"       HTTP::Daemon IO::Socket::SSL LWP LWP::Protocol::https Net::IP\n"
"       Text::Template UNIVERSAL::require Win32::Daemon Win32::Job Win32::OLE\n"
"       Win32::TieRegistry XML::TreePP'\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "They are only two lines:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"In the case of FusionInventory-Agent-Task-Deploy v2.0.3 the list of the "
"required and recommended Perl modules are the same that for v2.0.2, so there "
"is not needed any additional change."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"As the list of modules for FusionInventory-Agent has changed, it is "
"necessary to generate a new package Strawberry Perl Package."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "[[!template  id=info text=\"Note that this is an strange case and that is not totally necessary.\"]]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"You should start with a clean Strawberry Perl distribution too, so the "
"recommended steps are:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "Remember, this task can be done only from Microsoft Windows OS."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    # cd fusioninventory-agent-windows-installer\n"
"    # cd Perl\\Scripts\n"
"    # .\\install-gnu-utilities-collection.bat\n"
"    # .\\uninstall-strawberry-perl.bat\n"
"    # .\\install-strawberry-perl.bat\n"
"    # .\\install-perl-modules-and-dependencies.bat\n"
"    # .\\delete-perl-modules-and-dependencies-temporary-files.bat\n"
"    # .\\build-strawberry-perl-package-for-fusioninventory-agent.bat\n"
"    # .\\uninstall-strawberry-perl.bat\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"Now you can load the new package and its associated files into your public "
"repository of Strawberry Perl Packages for FusionInventory-Agent. This can "
"be a local repository; you only have to change the 'strawberry_pepfia_url' "
"variable of the file './Perl/Scripts/load-perl-environment'. For example, to "
"leave the default directory as the default repository, you only have to do "
"the following:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"     -declare -r strawberry_pepfia_url='https://github.com/downloads/tabad/fusioni\n"
"      nventory-agent-windows-installer'\n"
"     +declare -r strawberry_pepfia_url='file://c/.../fusioninventory-agent-windows\n"
"      -installer/Perl/Strawberry'\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "They are only two lines."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"            Remember, 'file://' is dependent of the OS and must be written as\n"
"            a absolute path. Make sure, in any case, that the value of the\n"
"            'strawberry_pepfia_url' variable is correct.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"Finally, you should change the following constants of the file './NSIS/ /"
