"      -declare -r strawberry_version='5.16.1.1'\n"
"      -declare -r strawberry_release='Aug 2012'\n"
"      +declare -r strawberry_version='5.16.2.1'\n"
"      +declare -r strawberry_release='Nov 2012'\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"   Update constant 'STRAWBERRY_RELEASE' of file './NSIS/\n"
"/FusionInventory.nsi' to adapt it to its new value:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"      Remember, probably you also will need to build a new Strawberry Perl\n"
"      Portable Edition Package for FusionInventory Agent.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title -
#, no-wrap
msgid "How to upgrade the agent and its tasks\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"   By taking a look at https://github.com/fusinv/fusioninventory-agent/tags and\n"
"https://github.com/fusinv/fusioninventory-agent-task-deploy/tags you see those\n"
"new releases are v2.2.6 and v2.0.3 respectively (it is true in the time I am\n"
"writing this; Oct 23, 2012). These are the changes you should to carry out.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"            Note that, in these cases, '2.2.6' and '2.0.3' are 'tags' in Git\n"
"            terminology; that is, in our case, stable releases. A tag makes\n"
"            reference, in last term, to a commit, therefore the name of the\n"
"            variable.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"   An important thing to take into account is that, probably, these new releases\n"
"require new, or simply different, Perl modules. Whether it is so, you should\n"
"build a new Strawberry Perl Portable Edition Package for FusionInventory Agent.\n"
"But before to do that, you should carry out two actions; a) to increase the\n"
"package build identifier and b) to update the list of required and recommended\n"
"Perl modules.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"            Note that the variable 'strawberry_pepfia_branch' is not necessary\n"
"            to change it in this case since the branch 2.2.x match with the\n"
"            branch of FusionInventory-Agent release 2.2.6.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"            Remember that you should reset 'strawberry_pepfia_build_id' to '1'\n"
"            whether you upgrade the Strawberry Perl distribution.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"   The second one is, most of the times, more tedious. You should check whether\n"
"there is new requirements or recommendations comparing the files 'Makefile.PL'\n"
"of each FusionInventory-Agent package you want to update. Then, whether there\n"
"are changes, you must update the respective variable 'fusinv_agent_mod_depen-\n"
"dences', 'fusinv_task_deploy_mod_dependences', 'fusinv_task_esx_mod_dependences'\n"
"or 'fusinv_task_network_mod_dependences' of './Perl/Scripts/load-perl-environ-\n"
"ment' file to reflect these changes.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"      Remember that, probably, you also need to update these variables whether\n"
"      you have upgraded the Strawberry Perl distribution.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "   Let's look at an example for FusionInventory-Agent.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"   In https://github.com/fusinv/fusioninventory-agent/tags you can see all\n"
"stable releases of FusionInventory-Agent. In that, below '2.2.6.zip - 2.2.6 re-\n"
"lease' appears the sequence '6f67b7d73c'; the short form for its SHA1 commit.\n"
"Do click on it, and after, do click on 'Browse code' (up and right). In the list\n"
"of files that appears, do click on file 'Makefile.PL' and write down the list\n"
"of required and recommended Perl modules (those lines started by 'requires ...'\n"
"and 'recommends ...', but not those lines started by 'text_requires ...')\n"
"commons to all operative systems and those specific for Microsoft Windows (those\n"
"lines under the condition '($OSNAME eq 'MSWin32')'). This list of Perl modules\n"
"should be the new value of the variable 'fusinv_agent_mod_dependences'. Like\n"
"this list is different of that for 2.2.5 release (repeat the previous process\n"
"for '2.2.5.zip - 2.2.5 release') you need change the value of the variable\n"
"'fusinv_agent_mod_dependences'.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "            Note that they are only two lines.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"   In the case of FusionInventory-Agent-Task-Deploy v2.0.3 the list of the\n"
"required and recommended Perl modules are the same that for v2.0.2, so there\n"
"is not needed any additional change.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"   As the list of modules for FusionInventory-Agent has changed, it is necessary\n"
"to generate a new Strawberry Perl Portable Edition Package.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"            Note that this is a strange case and that is not totally necessary\n"
"            because the Digest:MD5 Perl module is integrated into Strawberry\n"
"            Perl Portable Edition since its version v5.12.1.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"   You should start with a clean Strawberry Perl distribution too, so the\n"
"recommended steps are:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "            Remember, this task can be done only from Microsoft Windows OS.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"   > cd fusioninventory-agent-windows-installer\n"
"   > cd Perl\\Scripts\n"
"   > .\\install-gnu-utilities-collection.bat\n"
"   > .\\uninstall-strawberry-perl.bat\n"
"   > .\\install-strawberry-perl.bat\n"
